To add a batch file that provides auto-authentication to the VPN on the lock screen of a Windows PC, you can utilize the Group Policy Editor. Here's how you can do it:

Press the Windows key + R to open the Run dialog box. Type "gpedit.msc" and hit Enter to open the Group Policy Editor.

In the Group Policy Editor, navigate to "Computer Configuration" -> "Windows Settings" -> "Scripts (Startup/Shutdown)".

Double-click on "Startup" in the right pane to open the "Startup Properties" window.

Click on the "Add" button to add a new startup script.

In the "Add a Script" window, click on the "Browse" button and locate your batch file (.bat).

Select your batch file and click "Open".

Click "OK" to close the "Add a Script" window.

Back in the "Startup Properties" window, you should see your batch file listed. Click "OK" to save the changes.

Close the Group Policy Editor.
